headline: Tech Investors Worry About High Prices, Regulation
summary: Tech stocks stumbled Wednesday with investors voicing concerns about high valuations and burdensome new rules.  Nvidia and Palantir both fell 2% or more by midday, dragging down the Nasdaq composite by 1.6% and the S&P 500 by 1.1%.  “People are looking for excuses to sell tech and buy the rest of the market,” said Jay Hatfield, chief executive officer at Infrastructure Capital Advisors.
